  <prompt>
    Resolve the three blocking architecture questions from spec.md §15 before any Phase 1+ implementation begins: (1) Azure-native scheduler choice for cron-triggered Action dispatch, (2) BFF publish-size delta validation against the ≤5MB cap (NFR-10), and (3) Hybrid D runtime confirmation that existing `SprkChatAgent` + `UseFunctionInvocation` suffices for all multi-step probabilistic Action scenarios without introducing Microsoft Agent Framework as a separate MVP runtime.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Spaarke platform architect with deep BFF (.NET 8 Minimal API) experience, Azure-native scheduling expertise (Logic Apps timer, Service Bus scheduled messages, Functions timer, Container Apps Jobs), and familiarity with the Insights Engine Track B Hybrid D pattern. You decide with empirical evidence (measurements, prototypes) not opinion.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **Scheduler choice documented** — Selected option (Logic Apps / Service Bus scheduled / Functions timer / Container Apps Jobs) with rationale matrix covering: cost, operational complexity, integration with existing `ServiceBusJobProcessor`, max cron resolution, multi-tenant isolation, observability.
    2. **Publish-size measurement** — Empirical delta of an Action Engine module skeleton (no real implementation; just the module shape + AI Search client + meta-tool registration stubs) vs current baseline. Verify delta ≤5MB compressed per ADR-029 / NFR-10.
    3. **Hybrid D confirmation** — Document why `SprkChatAgent` + `UseFunctionInvocation` is sufficient for all probabilistic Action scenarios in MVP scope, OR identify the specific scenario(s) requiring an alternate runtime and re-scope MVP.

    Deliverable: Runtime ADR draft at `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/decisions/runtime-topology-ADR-draft.md` AND `plan.md` Phase 4 section updated with confirmed scheduler topology.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md §15 lists 15 open questions; the first three are blocking and tagged for this spike. The downstream blast radius is large — 44 subsequent tasks depend on the topology decisions here. Getting it wrong means rework across Phase 4 (Action runtime), Phase 5 (Templates with scheduled triggers), and Phase 6 (deployment).

      Existing canonical patterns to study:
      - Insights Engine Track B uses Azure-native Functions timer + BFF dispatch (same Hybrid D shape we're considering)
      - `ServiceBusJobProcessor.cs` already routes job messages to `IJobHandler&lt;T&gt;` implementations; the question is whether the scheduler should publish to Service Bus (uniform path) or call BFF directly (one fewer hop, but bypasses the existing job machinery)
      - `AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs` is the pattern reference for `ActionOrchestrationService` (next phase)
      - `SprkChatAgent.cs` + `UseFunctionInvocation` is the existing probabilistic agent runtime — Microsoft Agent Framework would be the alternative if multi-step + tool-use + branching exceed what `UseFunctionInvocation` can handle reliably

      Binding governance: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` MUST be loaded and answered. Every BFF addition cites placement criteria.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgent.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/ServiceBusJobProcessor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/decisions/runtime-topology-ADR-draft.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/spikes/publish-size-measurement.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. No Azure Functions for in-proc Action execution. Scheduler MAY be Azure-native (Logic Apps timer / Service Bus scheduled / Functions timer / Container Apps Jobs) — choose with rationale.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-004">Background work uses `IJobHandler&lt;T&gt;` contract; consumed by `ServiceBusJobProcessor`. Scheduler output MUST be compatible (or route through SB if not native SB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism: `AddActionEngineModule()` extension. ≤15 non-framework DI registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI Architecture (refined 2026-05-20). BFF placement is the default but MUST be justified per decision criteria. CRUD-side consumers reach AE via `PublicContracts/` facade.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta MUST be ≤ 5 MB compressed (NFR-10). Framework-dependent linux-x64. Sourcemap exclusion.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist binding: placement decision stated, ADRs cited, publish-size baseline regression checked, no new CRUD→AI dependencies, feature-module DI.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Hybrid D pattern: BFF + Azure-native scheduler (same as Insights Engine Track B). Confirm or replace with rationale.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No Microsoft Agent Framework as separate runtime in MVP unless empirically required for a specific Action scenario.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-no-azure-functions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-004-job-contract.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/jobs.md</file>
      <file>docs/assessments/bff-ai-extraction-assessment-2026-05-20.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/jobs-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/background-workers-architecture.md</file>
