  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Scheduler choice document exists at `notes/spikes/scheduler-comparison.md` with a 4-row comparison matrix and explicit recommendation. Rationale cites ADR-001 and ADR-004.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size measurement document exists at `notes/spikes/publish-size-measurement.md` with before/after compressed sizes and delta ≤ 5 MB. If exceeded, mitigations are documented and either resolved or escalated as a risk.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Hybrid D validation document exists at `notes/spikes/hybrid-d-validation.md` with scenario-by-scenario assessment of every MVP-scope probabilistic Action. Conclusion: SprkChatAgent + UseFunctionInvocation suffices, OR specific scenarios deferred to R2 with rationale.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Runtime ADR draft exists at `notes/decisions/runtime-topology-ADR-draft.md` in ADR-001-style format (Status / Context / Decision / Consequences).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`plan.md` Phase 4 references the confirmed scheduler choice. Risk Register R1 + R2 statuses updated.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Spike artifacts (module skeleton from step 4) reverted; `git status` shows only new files under `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/` (and `plan.md` update).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Baseline build still passes: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Reference spec.md §15 questions 1–3 (the blocking ones). Questions 4–15 are non-blocking and resolved by their owning phase tasks.

    The publish-size measurement is the highest-risk axis. If the skeleton already eats >2 MB compressed before any real implementation, expect Phase 4+ to push over budget. In that case, propose package boundary changes (e.g., consume AI Search via existing client rather than new direct reference) and re-measure.

    Do NOT introduce Microsoft Agent Framework as a separate runtime in MVP. If a scenario truly requires it, defer that scenario to R2 — do not balloon the MVP runtime surface.

    `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` answers must be visible in the ADR draft. The PR for task 014 (BFF module skeleton) will cite this ADR draft as its placement justification.
  </notes>

